Syntactically, blocks look like this:
<pre class="sh_ruby">
{ |blockname|     ...blahblahblah... }
</pre>

I've only used them in loops, like this from my notdpkg.fcgi script:
<pre class="sh_ruby">
    dpkglist = rq.keys().sort()
    i = 0
    dpkglist.each { |dpkg|
        i = i + 1
        if i < 50
            puts "<a href=\"/blog/dpkg/#{dpkg}.html\">#{dpkg}</a><br/>"
        end
    }
</pre>

In [[Ruby]], blocks are closely related to [[Ruby Proc]].

